## 2. TRADEMARKS, TRADE DRESS & PROPRIETARY MARKS

### 2.1 Lost Limb Riders® - Federal Trademark Protection
"Lost Limb Riders," associated logos, insignia, color combinations, and all visual representations are registered trademarks of Lost Limb Riders, Inc. Use without authorization violates 15 U.S.C. § 1127.

**Permitted Trademark Uses:** Authorized representatives only, in official capacity, as directed by Proprietors.

**Prohibited Trademark Uses:**
- Any commercial or non-commercial use without written authorization
- Registration, attempted registration, or claim of ownership
- Incorporation into domain names, social media handles, or applications
- Use as part of company names, product names, or service marks
- Modification, distortion, or alteration of any kind
- Use likely to dilute, tarnish, or blur the distinctive quality
- Use in connection with products or services other than Lost Limb Riders' official offerings
- Use in comparative advertising or disparaging context
- Use in any jurisdiction without prior written consent

### 2.2 "I Can. I Will." - Proprietary Motto
This phrase is the exclusive personal property and motto of John Thompson. It is NOT in the public domain. Any use, registration, or claim requires explicit written authorization from John Thompson personally.

**Trademark Dilution Notice:** Unauthorized use constitutes trademark dilution under 15 U.S.C. § 1125(c) and triggers statutory damages.

### 2.3 Logo Files & Brand Assets
All visual brand materials, logos, color codes, typography, and graphic files are proprietary trade dress. Unauthorized reproduction or modification infringes protected trade dress rights.

