## 5. LIABILITY, INDEMNIFICATION & DAMAGES

### 5.1 Liquidated Damages
Proprietors reserve the right to seek liquidated damages for violations, calculated as:
- Statutory damages under 17 U.S.C. § 504: up to $150,000 per violation
- Trademark dilution damages under 15 U.S.C. § 1125(c): up to $300,000 per willful violation
- Trade secret misappropriation damages under 18 U.S.C. § 1836: treble damages plus attorney fees
- Actual damages: 100% of profits derived from unauthorized use
- Punitive damages: discretionary, for willful violations
- Attorney fees and costs: full recovery from violator

### 5.2 Injunctive Relief
Proprietors are entitled to immediate injunctive relief, including temporary restraining orders and preliminary injunctions, without posting bond. Proprietors do NOT need to prove irreparable harm or inadequacy of legal remedies.

### 5.3 Indemnification
Users indemnify and hold harmless Proprietors from:
- All claims arising from user's breach of this Agreement
- All costs of enforcement, including attorney fees
- All damages from unauthorized disclosure or use
- All third-party claims arising from user's conduct
- Statutory damages and treble damages where applicable

### 5.4 No Limitation of Liability
NO provision limits Proprietors' recovery for:
- Trademark infringement
- Trade secret misappropriation
- Copyright infringement
- Breach of confidentiality
- Violations of law

