## 6. ENFORCEMENT & LEGAL REMEDIES

### 6.1 Cumulative Rights
Proprietors' rights are cumulative. Exercise of one remedy does not waive others.

### 6.2 Right to Pursue All Remedies
Proprietors reserve the right to pursue:
- Federal civil litigation in any jurisdiction
- State court litigation
- Criminal referral to law enforcement
- International legal action under applicable treaties
- Demand for immediate return/destruction of materials
- Seizure of infringing materials
- Disclosure demands under subpoena power
- Expedited court proceedings

### 6.3 Attorney Fees & Costs
In any enforcement action, losing party pays 100% of Proprietors' attorney fees, expert witness fees, court costs, and all litigation expenses.

### 6.4 Statute of Limitations
Proprietors may pursue claims within the maximum statute of limitations for each violation:
- Copyright: 3 years from discovery
- Trademark: 3 years from discovery
- Trade secrets: perpetual (for actual trade secrets)
- Breach of contract: 4-6 years depending on state

